metadata.description:
#1 of 8 psychogeography photographs taken while Flâneuring down Walpole Lane 19.05.2022

Lat 50° 43’ 34.236” N
Long 1° 50’ 38.316” W

CatMonkeyRun is on a mission for silent images with nothing to say, fishing in the rivers of light.

Psychogeography - the exploration of geographical environments, typically a city or town, considered with regard to their influence on the mind or on behaviour.

Flâneur - to wander detached from society with no purpose other than to observer contemporary life and landscapes.

CatMonkeyRun NFT's include a translucent artist’s chop mark.
